Key Match Events: Angola's goalkeeper Neblu received a straight red card for handling outside the penalty area.
Gelson Dala scored two goals for Angola.
Namibia's Lubeni Pombili Haukongo received a red card.
Mabululu scored Angola's third goal with a stylish right-footed effort.
Angola progressed to the AFCON quarter-finals for just the third time.
Post-Match Reflections: Angola's coach Gonçalves now looks to go at least one step further this time around.
Namibia will look back on the early red card to goalkeeper Neblú as a missed opportunity.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Angola progressed to the quarter-finals of the Africa Cup of Nations for just the third-ever time.
The match saw both sides reduced to 10 men in the first half.
